<h1>Getting Started</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col col-lg-6">
    <div style="margin-top: 20px">
        <h3>Steps for getting started (example on right)</h3>
        <ol>
            <li>Add references to <a href="http://angularjs.org/" target="_blank">AngularJS</a>.</li>
            <li>Add references to <a href="https://github.com/esvit/ng-table/">ngTable</a>'s javascript and css files.</li>
            <li>Where you declare your app module, add ngTable:<br>
                <code>angular.module('myApp',['ngTable']);</code>
            </li>
            <li>In your html file within the controller where you plan to use ng-table, add:<br>
            <code>&lt;table ng-table&gt;...&lt;/table&gt;</code></li>
            <li>We are going to define a basic style for table in style.css:
<pre style="margin-top:10px" class="prettyprint">
.ng-table {
    border: 1px solid #000;
}
</pre>
            </li>
            <li>In your javascript file within the controller where you plan to use<br>ng-table, lets add data that our table will use:<br> </li>
<pre style="margin-top:10px" class="prettyprint">
$scope.users = [{name: "Moroni", age: 50},
                {name: "Tiancum", age: 43},
                {name: "Jacob", age: 27},
                {name: "Nephi", age: 29},
                {name: "Enos", age: 34}];
</pre>
            <li>Now create your table rows:<br>
                <code>ng-repeat="user in users"</code>
            </li>
            </ol>
    </div>
</div>
<div class="col col-lg-6">

